<subSubSection pageId="42" pageNumber="1175" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="42.[178,1086,852,1166]" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175">
C o m m e n t: The original description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1787" box="[632,835,852,873]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Staphylinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tricolor">
<emphasis box="[632,835,852,873]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175">Staphylinus tricolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is based on an unspecified number of 
<typeStatus box="[340,429,882,903]" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175">syntypes</typeStatus>
from &quot;Daniae Boletis&quot; (
<bibRefCitation author="FABRICIUS J" box="[681,853,881,903]" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175" refId="ref28159" refString="FABRICIUS J. C. (1787): Mantissa insectorum sistens eorum species nuper detectas adiectis characteribus genericis, differentiis specificis, emendationibus, observationibus. 1. - Hafniae: C. G. Proft: 348 pp." type="book" year="1787">FABRICIUS 1787</bibRefCitation>
). The interpretation of this rather common and widespread Palaearctic species had largely been uncontroversial until, based on an examination of a putative type, 
<bibRefCitation author="DRUGMAND D" box="[686,881,940,962]" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175" pagination="241 - 252" refId="ref28116" refString="DRUGMAND D. (1994): Le groupe d'especes proches de Xantholinus jarrigei COIFFAIT, un veritable imbroglio systematique (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France 99 (3): 241 - 252." type="journal article" year="1994">DRUGMAND (1994)</bibRefCitation>
stated that this type was conspecific with 
<taxonomicName authority="(GRAVENHORST, 1802)" baseAuthorityName="GRAVENHORST" baseAuthorityYear="1802" box="[398,857,969,991]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lithocharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ochracea">
<emphasis box="[398,616,969,990]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175">Lithocharis ochracea</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="GRAVENHORST J" box="[630,850,969,991]" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175" refId="ref28337" refString="GRAVENHORST J. L. C. (1802): Coleoptera microptera Brunsvicensia. - Brunsuigae: 206 pp." type="book" year="1802">GRAVENHORST, 1802</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, that consequently the binomen for the species previously referred to as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="GRAVENHORST" baseAuthorityYear="1802" box="[701,921,998,1019]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lithocharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ochracea">
<emphasis box="[701,921,998,1019]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175">Lithocharis ochracea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was 
<taxonomicName authority="(FABRICIUS)" baseAuthorityName="FABRICIUS" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Staphylinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tricolor">
<emphasis box="[978,1085,998,1020]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175">L. tricolor</emphasis>
(FABRICIUS)
</taxonomicName>
, and that the species which had been interpreted as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1787" box="[833,1039,1028,1049]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Xantholinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tricolor">
<emphasis box="[833,1039,1028,1049]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175">Xantholinus tricolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was without valid name. Thus, he described it as 
<taxonomicName authority="DRUGMAND, 1994" authorityName="DRUGMAND" authorityYear="1994" box="[650,948,1057,1078]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Xantholinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="meyeri">
<emphasis box="[650,749,1057,1078]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175">X. meyeri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="DRUGMAND D" box="[757,948,1057,1078]" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175" pagination="241 - 252" refId="ref28116" refString="DRUGMAND D. (1994): Le groupe d'especes proches de Xantholinus jarrigei COIFFAIT, un veritable imbroglio systematique (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France 99 (3): 241 - 252." type="journal article" year="1994">DRUGMAND, 1994</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. In an article published in the same year, however, 
<bibRefCitation author="CICERONI A" box="[574,747,1086,1108]" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175" pagination="97 - 119" refId="ref27861" refString="CICERONI A. (1994): Revisione delle specie italiane del genere Leptacinus ERICHSON con note sinonimiche su alcuni Xantholinini europei e nordafricani. - Bollettino del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Verona 18 (1991): 97 - 119." type="journal article" year="1994">CICERONI (1994)</bibRefCitation>
found that 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1787" box="[870,1078,1086,1107]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Xantholinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tricolor">
<emphasis box="[870,1078,1086,1107]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175">Xantholinus tricolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which he interpreted in the traditional sense, had four synonyms, all of them older than 
<taxonomicName authorityName="DRUGMAND" authorityYear="1994" box="[178,275,1145,1166]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Xantholinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="meyeri">
<emphasis box="[178,275,1145,1166]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175">X. meyeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="43" lastPageNumber="1176" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="42.[178,1085,1182,1350]" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175">
<bibRefCitation author="HERMAN L" box="[178,347,1182,1204]" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175" pagination="1 - 82" refId="ref28358" refString="HERMAN L. H. (2001): Nomenclatural changes in the Staphylinidae (Insecta: Coleoptera). - Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 264: 1 - 82." type="journal article" year="2001">HERMAN (2001)</bibRefCitation>
doubted and refused to accept Drugmand´s conclusions arguing that 
<bibRefCitation author="DRUGMAND D" box="[178,375,1211,1233]" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175" pagination="241 - 252" refId="ref28116" refString="DRUGMAND D. (1994): Le groupe d'especes proches de Xantholinus jarrigei COIFFAIT, un veritable imbroglio systematique (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France 99 (3): 241 - 252." type="journal article" year="1994">DRUGMAND (1994)</bibRefCitation>
had failed to produce evidence that he had actually examined a true (and the only) 
<typeStatus box="[340,384,1241,1262]" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175">type</typeStatus>
specimen, that 
<typeStatus box="[555,599,1241,1262]" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175">type</typeStatus>
material in the Fabricius collection had been known to be replaced by non-type specimens, that the &quot;changes proposed by Drugmand [were] too radical to be made so casually&quot;, and that the original description was not in agreement with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="GRAVENHORST" baseAuthorityYear="1802" box="[341,558,1328,1349]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lithocharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ochracea">
<emphasis box="[341,558,1328,1349]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175">Lithocharis ochracea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="42.[178,1085,1365,1592]" lastBlockId="43.[178,1085,219,504]" lastPageId="43" lastPageNumber="1176" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175">
Alexey Solodovnikov (
<collectionCode box="[415,495,1366,1388]" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175">NHMD</collectionCode>
) located 
<specimenCount box="[591,741,1366,1388]" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
labelled as [
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[874,992,1366,1387]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Staphylinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[874,992,1366,1387]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175">Staphylinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
] 
<emphasis box="[1008,1085,1366,1387]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175">tricolor</emphasis>
in the Fabricius collection, one in the Copenhagen and one in the Kiel collection. (The latter is currently housed in the 
<collectionCode box="[513,593,1425,1446]" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175">NHMD</collectionCode>
, too.) The slightly damaged specimen from the Copenhagen collection had been examined and evidently re-mounted by Drugmand; it is a female 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="GRAVENHORST" baseAuthorityYear="1802" box="[275,493,1483,1504]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lithocharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ochracea">
<emphasis box="[275,493,1483,1504]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175">Lithocharis ochracea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
labelled &quot;S: tricolor [evidently a curator label] / Type [a red printed recent label] / D. Drugmand Rev. 1992, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1787" box="[708,905,1512,1534]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lithocharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tricolor">Lithocharis tricolor</taxonomicName>
(F.), = 
<taxonomicName authority="(Grav)" baseAuthorityName="Grav" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Paederus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ochraceus">ochraceus (Grav)</taxonomicName>
/ zmuc 00037679&quot;. The specimen from the Kiel collection bears the original label &quot;tricolor&quot; in Fabricius´ handwriting. Although it is in very poor condition (abdomen missing), it is undoubtedly conspecific with the traditional interpretation of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1787" box="[970,1078,219,240]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lithocharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="1176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tricolor">
<emphasis box="[970,1078,219,240]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="1176">X. tricolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. While this specimen fits the original description, that from the Copenhagen collection clearly does not (&quot;Caput atrum, nitidum&quot;; &quot;Abdomen nigrum&quot;). Moreover, it would seem most unlikely that 
<bibRefCitation author="FABRICIUS J" box="[379,564,307,329]" pageId="43" pageNumber="1176" refId="ref28159" refString="FABRICIUS J. C. (1787): Mantissa insectorum sistens eorum species nuper detectas adiectis characteribus genericis, differentiis specificis, emendationibus, observationibus. 1. - Hafniae: C. G. Proft: 348 pp." type="book" year="1787">FABRICIUS (1787)</bibRefCitation>
attributed 
<specimenCount box="[682,835,307,329]" pageId="43" pageNumber="1176" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
that are so different in body size and numerous other characters to one and the same species. Therefore, it is concluded that only the specimen from the Kiel collection represents a true type and that the specimen from the Copenhagen collection is no 
<typeStatus box="[707,788,395,416]" pageId="43" pageNumber="1176">syntype</typeStatus>
, but was added to the collection subsequently. In order to stabilize the prevailing interpretation of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1787" box="[928,1037,424,445]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lithocharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="1176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tricolor">
<emphasis box="[928,1037,424,445]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="1176">X. tricolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus box="[178,257,453,474]" pageId="43" pageNumber="1176">syntype</typeStatus>
from the Kiel collection is designated as the 
<typeStatus box="[729,825,453,475]" pageId="43" pageNumber="1176">lectotype</typeStatus>
. It was re-mounted using the original pin.
</paragraph>
